File: Telkom JOHANNESBURG - Telkom's share price increased by almost 15 percent after the company released a profit update. The company confirmed that its headline profit for the past six months will increase by 15 to 25 percent. Group revenue was flat despite growth at Telkom Mobile, but the company says it's focusing on managing costs. READ: Telkom to offer financial services The group performance was sound despite a difficult trading environment due to the adverse impact of COVID-19 on the economy. Group revenue showed resilience in the face of the pandemic, remaining broadly flat compared to the prior period. The mobile business continued its growth trajectory, placing Telkom Mobile as the third-largest mobile operator in South Africa.